Read about the difference between window, screen and document in javaScript
    The Window object represents the browser window or tab that the user is currently viewing. It provides access to various browser properties 
and methods, such as the location of the window, the history of the browser, and the ability to open and close new windows.

    The Screen object represents the user's screen or display. It provides information about the size and resolution of the screen, as well as other
properties such as the color depth and available space.

    The Document object represents the HTML document that is currently loaded in the browser window.
